Contributory Negligence  often produces harsh results and many jurisdictions use the <strong>LAST CLEAR CHANCE DOCTRINE</strong> to <strong>allow</strong> a <strong>negligent</strong> plaintiff to still <strong>recover</strong> where <strong>if</strong> the <strong>defendant</strong> had the <strong>last clear opportunity</strong> to <strong>avoid</strong> the <strong>accident</strong>.